review_blob: Nocturnal pour with thin burnt brown head. aroma alone warrants purchasing this beer. Bitter coffee, chocolate, smoky oat maltiness, quite elevating. Taste is coffee, oats, alcohol, chocolate and glory. Hide your coffee maker and wake up right.
beer_name: Terrapin Wake-n-Bake Coffee Oatmeal Imperial Stout

review_blob: Olfactory paragon exuding effervescence with the finesse only founders could conjure. Hard to stop imbibing this fresh hoppiness, until you run out. If youre into juicy citrus goodness check this out.

This is an intense beer in every way so be prepared. Tongue puzzling. I have had a fresh bottle and an aged bottle of this, both delicious but in different ways. I would suggest drinking one fresh and letting a few age for a year or so. Bitter and beautiful with a sweetness that lingers on the tongue. This is a triple IPA and taste like what I think a triple IPA should taste like... absolutely amazing.

This IIPA really works well. A hoppy beer that provides all the bitter goodness one looks for in this style of beer. The aroma is citrus and bitterness wrapped in a balanced malt. I really like this sticky sucker.

Wakes the taste buds up. Has a fruity alcohol punch to it that works quite elegantly. I enjoy the way it makes you feel like youre drinking an actual beer. Wonderful sweet warm flavor lingers well after the last sip. A splendid time.

Excellent IPA that delivers everything you want in a good beer. Bitter but well balanced, this beer is worthy of being in the regular rotation for certain. If you havent tried this beauty yet do yourself a favor and grab some.

This is a successful combination of two styles of beer unfortunately it just didnt work for me. If you like german hefeweizens and IPAs you will probably love this beer. I personally dont care much for hefeweizens and was hoping this was more of an IPA with a tinge of hefeweizen but it is more like equal parts of both. Not super hoppy, the alcohol is hidden nicely, banana yeasty vibe to it. I have to say this is an interesting beer that I am glad to have tried, just not my thing.

Decent imperial IPA but not what I was hoping for. Very drinkable although it didnt pack the punch I look for in this style of beer. Worth a try but I wouldnt worry too much if you cant find it. A funky citrus flavor lacking any serious hop bite.
beer_name: Laughing Dog Alpha Dog Imperial IPA

review_blob: A hop bomb of delight. Pungent hop presence beautifully balanced within the beer making this a true pleasure. A skunky hop aroma that is intoxicating on its own. Really bitter but in all the right ways. If I could drink this all the time I would.
Highly drinkable double IPA, wish the hops played a larger role in this one. The alcohol comes through adding a nice touch. If you like a sweet sticky beer this will treat you well.

The mouthfeel is phenomenally smooth and smile inducing. Aroma is fruity, solid maltiness and a touch of alcohol. Well balanced beer that has a hop bite with a sweet maltiness blending together masterfully. The papaya is kind of in the background which I like very much, its there but in good moderation. You do not taste any alcohol in this one. Keep em coming.
beer_name: Cigar City Papaya India Pale Ale

review_blob: This beer is incredible. At first I was a bit overwhelmed by the smokiness but after a few sips the glorious nature of this beer came through and completely took me by surprise. You may think a smoked double IPA is a bad idea, it is not. This is genius. The aroma was a little strange, smoky, bitter, slight citrus/grassyness. Once this settles down it goes down smooth and silky, had a pork rindish vibe that for some reason I loved. A unique beauty that I highly recommend especially if you want something different that is done well. smoky heaven.
beer_name: Terrapin Georgia Theatre Session: Hoptaneous Combustion

review_blob: Bitter bomb beauty. Citrus, pine and grassy hop flavor with some zest. As it warms the alcohol comes through a bit but not a problem in my book. Dry finish, the aroma is gorgeous with a bitter bite to it. Enjoyable stuff.

A decent pale ale, nothing too exciting about this one. I had a bottle that was a bit old and it showed. On tap this beer tasted significantly better, but was mellow, simple and somewhat unimpressive.
beer_name: Olde Hickory Table Rock Pale Ale

review_blob: Beautiful IPA, citrus and bitterness harmonize. Golden orange, white head, alcohol hidden nicely. You can drink this one all night. Not the most complex of IPAs but a solid beer that I will be drinking more of.

No IPA characteristics you want are in this one. Malty mess but this is drinkable. Usually marine life on beer means quality, not on this one. If you havent had this youre not missing much. That non-sensical ideation got me.
This is disgusting, but strangely I understand why people drink this beer. Dont drink unless necessary.
Sweet sticky resinous beauty. Alcohol presence buried deep, a bitter beer but was expecting more of a hop bite in this one at 100 IBU. Great citrus notes and piney/grassy vibe compliment this one.

Fantastic effort by Bells. When fresh this beer will amaze you with a stupendous balance of hops, honey, malt and citrus that you wont believe until you taste. If I could I would drink this beer every day. If you want to know what a perfectly balanced IIPA taste like, look no further.
Earthy tone, nice spice flavor. A great sweet taste that balances well with the hop bitterness. Easy to drink and a pleasant difference in taste from most other IIPAs.
Super drinkable IIPA. Not exactly the hop bomb I was hoping for but the malt backbone works pretty well. This is a somewhat subdued IIPA that lacks the bitter hoppiness I enjoy. Give it a try.
A well balanced pale ale that lets you know youre drinking a beer in a good way. Great hops presence and bitterness. Drink this beer.
A great session beer, but beyond that nothing else. For a mass produced brew this one impresses. When in a pinch grab some Stellas and you wont be disappointed. Nice Tasting lager.
